The line `this.dataSource.next(this.data);` notifies that data is changed and changes are reflected then.

***Not tested but try if that works:***

    deleteUser(user) {
      this.dataSource.data.splice(this.dataSource.data.indexOf(user), 1);
      this.dataSource.next(this.dataSource.data);
    }

The `mat-table` will not detect the changes in your `dataSource` if it is changed through mutation, it will only re-render if the array reference is changed. Try updating the `data` in the `dataSource` immutably after you use your `splice` function like below.
```js
this.dataSource.data.splice(this.dataSource.data.indexOf(user), 1);
this.dataSource.data = [...this.dataSource.data];
```

Or if you have a unique value, say `id` in `user`, you can use [`filter`][1] since it creates a new array.
```js
deleteUser (id) {
    this.dataSource.data = this.dataSource.data.filter(user =&gt; user.position !== id);
}
```
where `id` is the `id` of the `user` you want to delete.

  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter

